Until now, it has been the preserve of those willing to hunt for their supper – or at least hunt out restaurants serving it.

Now, however, grouse has come to the high street.

Marks & Spencer has become the first retailer to stock whole wild red grouse – and bosses are expecting the £10 oven-ready dish to fly off the shelves.

